<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,150,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,537,186,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported from mud and sediments containing organisms such as sponge (
<taxonomicName box="[325,504,222,249]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondriidae" genus="Halicondria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[325,462,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Halicondria</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
), algae (
<taxonomicName authority=", Plocanium" authorityName="Plocanium" box="[602,892,222,249]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Cystoclonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[602,756,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Cystoclonium</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[771,892,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Plocanium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), pycnogonids, etc., from 
<collectingCountry box="[1191,1311,222,248]" name="Germany" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Helgoland</collectingCountry>
, North Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[205,344,258,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="83 - 173" refId="ref20607" refString="Viets, K. (1927 a) Die Halacaridae der Nordsee. Zeitschrift fur Wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 130, 83 - 173." type="journal article" year="1927">Viets 1927a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,150,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,294,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was found in Novaja Semlja, Murmansk, 
<collectingCountry box="[902,1022,294,320]" name="Greenland" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Greenland</collectingCountry>
, eastern and western North Atlantic, and Baltic Sea from tidal and subtidal substrata, mainly among algae in marine and brackish water (Hodge 1860; 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[268,404,366,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="83 - 173" refId="ref20607" refString="Viets, K. (1927 a) Die Halacaridae der Nordsee. Zeitschrift fur Wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 130, 83 - 173." type="journal article" year="1927">Viets 1927a</bibRefCitation>
; Newell 1947; Bartsch 1972, 2009; 
<bibRefCitation author="Green, J. &amp; MacQuitty, M." box="[808,1099,366,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="1 - 178" refId="ref16549" refString="Green, J. &amp; MacQuitty, M. (1987) Halacarid Mites. Synopses of the British Fauna, New Series, 36, 1 - 178." type="journal article" year="1987">Green &amp; MacQuitty 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, H." box="[1109,1223,366,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" refId="ref12394" refString="Abe, H. (1998) Rhombognathine Mites. Taxonomy, Phylogeny, and Biogeography. Hokkaido University Press, Sapporo, 219 pp." type="book" year="1998">Ab√© 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
